definitions.definition: Any of many aquatic photosynthetic organisms , including the seaweeds , whose size ranges from a single cell to giant kelps and whose biochemistry and forms are very diverse, some being eukaryotic .

main_definition: ( biology ) Any of many aquatic photosynthetic organisms , including the seaweeds , whose size ranges from a single cell to giant kelps and whose biochemistry and forms are very diverse, some being eukaryotic .
